# npx Invocation for agent-browser and mcporter

## Overview

**MANDATORY**: When using `agent-browser` or `mcporter`, invoke them with `npx`.

## Required Command Forms

- Use `npx agent-browser ...`
- Use `npx mcporter ...`

## Do Not Use

- `agent-browser ...`
- `mcporter ...`

## Rationale

These tools may not be installed globally in every environment. Using `npx` ensures the correct project/local executable resolution path is used consistently.

## Examples

```bash
npx agent-browser open https://example.com
npx agent-browser snapshot -i
npx mcporter list context-7 --schema --output json
```

## Scope

Apply this rule whenever browser automation tasks use the `agent-browser` skill or MCP tasks use the `mcporter` skill.
